'''Greizhen mo Ullhor''' is a character in the [[Season 3|third season]]. He is portrayed by [[Clifford Barry]]. Greizhen mo Ullhor is a slave-trader in the city of [[Astapor]], on the coast of [[Slaver's Bay]].

sections.Biography:
===Background===
Greizen mo Ullhor is of the [[Good Masters]], the ruling elite of the city. He is an immensely wealthy [[Slavery|slaver]] who has grown rich from the training and trading of the [[Unsullied]] warrior-eunuchs.

===Season 3===

Greizhen accompanies fellow Good Master [[Kraznys mo Nakloz]] and a third Good Master for negotiations with [[Daenerys Targaryen]] and is amused by Kraznys' comments about her. When Daenerys states that she wants to buy not just the fully-trained Unsullied but the slaves in training as well, Greizhen opposes, concerned that if these half-trained warriors fail on the battlefield it would shame Astapor.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Walk of Punishment]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

[[File:KraznysGreizhen.jpg|thumb|right|250px|Greizhen and Kraznys about to deliver the Unsullied]]

Greizhen is present at one of Astapor's plazas for the conclusion of the transaction with Daenerys: the Unsullied and the half-trained boys in exchange for her [[dragon]] [[Drogon]]. He is killed when Daenerys orders to Unsullied to kill all the Good Masters, slave-drivers and soldiers in the city, sparing only the children, and liberate all the slaves.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[And Now His Watch is Ended]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;
